# LoadZone Testing

- Use the smallest test layer that proves the behavior: schema/unit first, integration for server actions and data flows, E2E only for golden paths.
- Add or update tests when changing validation, business rules, auth boundaries, or fixing regressions.
- Prefer colocated tests near the feature or under the app-level `__tests__` folder when the test exercises route behavior.
- Mock external services and unstable browser APIs. Keep database-backed tests focused on one contract at a time.
- A bug fix is not complete until the failure mode is reproducible through a targeted automated check or a documented manual repro when automation is not practical.
- Avoid low-signal snapshot or smoke tests that do not assert user-visible behavior or business rules.
